HEADWORD: Zilla
<hw>Zil"la</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Bot.)</fld> <def>A
low, thorny, suffrutescent, cruciferous plant (<spn>Zilla
myagroides</spn>) found in the deserts of Egypt. Its leaves are boiled
in water, and eaten, by the Arabs.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

